        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-19T23:18:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "What\u0027s the lifetime of this buffer, and who owns the destruction?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 58
      },
      "revId": "6557c9917915b24e79508b4820f100addac94bbb",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "d6db6368_9e13e740",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/videoplayback/videoplayback-render-target.h",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 37,
      "author": {
        "id": 1414904
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-20T00:38:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As far as I can tell, VideoPlayer, which calls this method, retains ownership of buffer and is responsible for its destruction.",
      "parentUuid": "ee62f305_ff5a2546",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 37,
        "startChar": 22,
        "endLine": 37,
        "endChar": 58
      },
      "revId": "6557c9917915b24e79508b4820f100addac94bbb",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "cb31c396_e7eac0fc",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/videoplayback/videoplayback-utils.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 32,
      "author": {
        "id": 1233742
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-19T23:18:13Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Regex is fairly expensive, especially given the size of the data since it will search the entire string.  Can this be implemented as a loop over the characters instead of regex?\n\nAlternatively, it looks like this comes from VideoPlayerImpl::queuePicture, which stores the values that are being parsed here into Frame*, including a headerlen so it can be easily skipped over.  Could they be accessed directly from the Frame* and the header skipped instead?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 29,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 32,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "6557c9917915b24e79508b4820f100addac94bbb",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "2dd5a8b5_27056437",
        "filename": "android/android-emu/android/videoplayback/videoplayback-utils.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 32,
      "author": {
        "id": 1414904
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-03-20T00:38:31Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Unfortunately the interface with VideoPlayer is a little bit wonky. The VideoPlayerRenderTarget only gets the image data passed to it via setPixelBuffer() and the only public VideoPlayer methods are things like start() and stop(), so I can\u0027t be clever and attempt to recover frame data from the owner of the VideoPlayer instance and send it to the render target when calling renderBuffer().\n\nImplemented a single loop to read the header. In the worst case it will still read the whole buffer when there are too few tokens in the buffer, but in the average case it will properly short-circuit once all the expected header tokens are processed.",
      "parentUuid": "cb31c396_e7eac0fc",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 29,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 32,
        "endChar": 70
      },
      "revId": "6557c9917915b24e79508b4820f100addac94bbb",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
